# Documentation System Guide

## Documentation Generation

Documentation is generated using the `docs:generate` command:

```bash
php artisan docs:generate
```

This command creates documentation in the `docs/` directory with the following structure:

- `api.md`: API documentation
- `features.md`: Feature documentation
- `setup.md`: Setup guide
- `contributing.md`: Contribution guide

## Documentation Components

The documentation system is implemented in [app/Console/Commands/GenerateDocsCommand.php](mdc:app/Console/Commands/GenerateDocsCommand.php) and includes:

- API endpoint documentation
- Authentication documentation
- Error handling documentation
- Feature documentation
- Setup and configuration guides
- Contribution guidelines

## GitHub Pages Integration

Documentation is automatically deployed to GitHub Pages through the workflow defined in [.github/workflows/pages.yml](mdc:.github/workflows/pages.yml).

The workflow:
1. Generates documentation
2. Builds the documentation site
3. Deploys to GitHub Pages

## Documentation Structure

Each documentation file follows a consistent structure:

1. Title and description
2. Main sections
3. Subsections with detailed information
4. Code examples where applicable
5. Configuration details
6. Usage instructions
